        <li><strong>Express.js:</strong> A minimal and flexible Node.js web application framework that provides a robust set of features for web and mobile applications.</li>
        <li><strong>EJS (Embedded JavaScript):</strong> A simple templating language that lets you generate HTML markup with plain JavaScript.</li>
        <li><strong>Bootstrap:</strong> A popular front-end framework for creating clean, responsive, and intuitive user interfaces.</li>
      </ul>
